Depends: python, ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description:Command-line interface to After the Deadline language checker
 atdtool is a command-line tools that contacts an After the Deadline language
 service and displays the errors reported by the service in a format very
 similar to gcc's, making it easy to integrate with other tools (vi, emacs).
 .
 After the Deadline is a language checker that is able to:
  - spell check contextually
  - check style
  - check grammar
 .
 The official server is free for personal use. They provide a free server for
 commercial use. atdtool can be used with the default server or with a custom
 one.
